(set: $anythingElse to "")

I've thought about this more than I've let on. When it comes to what happens after I'm gone, I [[have a clear vision — I want things done a particular way->disposition]] [[don't have strong opinions — I trust my family to decide what feels right->open-handed]].


:: open-handed
(set: $hasVision to "I didn't have strong opinions about the arrangements. What mattered to me was that my family felt free to do whatever brought them the most comfort — and that they knew I meant that.")

I didn't need everything done a particular way. But there are still a few things worth putting down, so the people I love aren't left guessing. When the time comes, I want to be [[buried->buried-details]] [[cremated->cremated-details]] [[something else->other-disposition]].


:: disposition
When the time comes, I want to be [[buried->buried-details]] [[cremated->cremated-details]] [[something else->other-disposition]].


:: buried-details
(set: $disposition to "buried")

Being buried felt right to me. There's something I liked about the idea of having a place — somewhere people could go, if they wanted to. It doesn't have to be grand. As for where:
(input-box: bind $burialPlace, "X", 1, "e.g. the churchyard in my hometown, near family, no strong preference...")

[[On the service...->service-type]]


:: cremated-details
(set: $disposition to "cremated")

Cremation felt right to me. I didn't want to take up much space — though I reserve the right to change my mind about that in other areas of life. As for my ashes:
(input-box: bind $ashesWishes, "X", 1, "e.g. scattered somewhere I loved, kept by the family, buried in the garden...")

[[On the service...->service-type]]


:: other-disposition
(set: $disposition to "other")

I had something a little different in mind — one of those options that's becoming more common and that felt more like me. What I'd want:
(input-box: bind $otherDisposition, "X", 1, "e.g. a natural burial, a woodland plot, body donation to science...")

[[On the service...->service-type]]


:: service-type
People handle this part very differently, and I think that's right. There's no wrong answer here — it's about what would actually help the people left behind, and whether that matches what I'd want them to remember. For a service, my preference was:
[[A formal funeral->service-formal]]
[[Something informal — a gathering, a celebration of life->service-informal]]
[[No service — just a quiet farewell->no-service]]
[[Whatever my family decides->service-family-decides]]


:: service-formal
(set: $serviceType to "a formal funeral service")

A proper funeral felt important to me. I wanted people to have a place to come, something to mark the occasion — not to be maudlin about it, but to acknowledge that something real had happened. For where I'd want it held, I was thinking [[a church or place of worship->service-requests]] [[a secular venue — somewhere that felt like me->service-requests]] [[the graveside or crematorium->service-requests]] [[wherever the family felt was right->service-requests]].


:: service-informal
(set: $serviceType to "an informal gathering — a celebration of life rather than a funeral")

I never liked the idea of something too formal. I'd rather people were comfortable — able to talk, share a drink, tell a story or two without feeling like they were doing it wrong. For where I'd want that to happen: [[somewhere with meaning to me->service-requests]] [[wherever the family decides->service-requests]].


:: no-service
(set: $serviceType to "no formal service")
(set: $serviceLocation to "")
(set: $serviceRequests to "")

A quiet farewell was enough for me. I didn't need a gathering, and I didn't want anyone to feel obliged to organise one on my behalf. The people who mattered to me would know.

For flowers — and people do ask about this — I'd want [[flowers, the more the better->flower-details]] [[just a few, nothing elaborate->flower-simple]] [[no flowers — I'd rather people donated to a cause->donation-details]] [[whatever feels right->flowers-no-pref]].


:: service-family-decides
(set: $serviceType to "whatever feels right to my family")
(set: $serviceLocation to "")
(set: $serviceRequests to "")

I genuinely meant it when I said I didn't mind. Whatever helped them most — that was what I wanted.

For flowers — and people do ask about this — I'd want [[flowers, the more the better->flower-details]] [[just a few, nothing elaborate->flower-simple]] [[no flowers — I'd rather people donated to a cause->donation-details]] [[whatever feels right->flowers-no-pref]].


:: service-requests
(set: $serviceLocation to "the location my family felt was right")

Is there anything specific I'd want included — or left out? A particular piece of music, a reading, a request about the tone of the thing. I'm not fussy, but if there was something:
(input-box: bind $serviceRequests, "X", 1, "e.g. no long eulogies, a particular hymn or song, keep it short, stories welcome...")

[[On flowers...->flowers]]


:: flowers
For flowers — and people do ask about this — I'd want [[flowers, the more the better->flower-details]] [[just a few, nothing elaborate->flower-simple]] [[no flowers — I'd rather people donated to a cause->donation-details]] [[whatever feels right->flowers-no-pref]].


:: flower-details
(set: $flowers to "flowers — as many as people wanted to bring")

I always thought flowers at a funeral made the room feel like life was still present in it. If there was a particular kind I'd want:
(input-box: bind $flowerPreference, "X", 1, "e.g. wildflowers, sunflowers, white flowers, nothing too formal...")

[[On the gathering...->gathering]]


:: flower-simple
(set: $flowers to "just a few simple flowers — nothing elaborate")
(set: $flowerPreference to "")

[[On the gathering...->gathering]]


:: flowers-no-pref
(set: $flowers to "no strong preference — whatever felt right")
(set: $flowerPreference to "")

[[On the gathering...->gathering]]


:: donation-details
(set: $flowers to "no flowers — I'd rather people donated to a cause that mattered to me")

There was something I'd want people to give to, if they were going to do anything. It felt more like me than cut flowers:
(input-box: bind $donationCause, "X", 1, "e.g. a cancer charity, the local hospice, an organisation I believed in...")

[[On the gathering...->gathering]]


:: gathering
After a funeral there's usually food, drink, and people telling stories they've been saving up. That part I didn't mind at all — in fact, I rather liked the thought of it. What I'd want it to look like:
(input-box: bind $gatheringWishes, "X", 2, "e.g. something at the house, a proper meal at a pub, tea and sandwiches, whatever people needed...")

[[One more thing...->song]]


:: song
Music is the thing that gets people, one way or another. I had thoughts about this. If there was something playing — at the service, or just somewhere in the day — I'd want:
(input-box: bind $songWish, "X", 1, "e.g. a particular song, something quiet, something that would make people smile, nothing in particular...")

[[And a reading...->reading]]


:: reading
I never expected anyone to stand up and perform something on my behalf. But if someone wanted to read a few words — something that felt right — I wouldn't have minded at all. If there was a reading, I'd want:
(input-box: bind $readingWish, "X", 1, "e.g. a favourite poem, a passage from a book, something a family member wrote, nothing formal...")

[[Last thing...->anything-else]]


:: anything-else
There's always something that doesn't fit anywhere else. A practical thing, maybe, or something I needed to say. Anything I'd want my family to know that I haven't covered:
(input-box: bind $anythingElse, "X", 2, "e.g. where important documents are, who to call, something I'd want said, or nothing at all...")
